# Website Presentational Label Props

Applies when authoring or reviewing a presentational component (blocks, cards, rows, sections) under `website/src/app/ui/components/`.

Authority: `docs/invariants/website.md` W42.

## Rule

Presentational components MUST NOT accept a `t: (key: string) => string` (or any `Translator`) prop. The screen owns translation; the component receives **already-resolved label strings** as explicit props.

The screen binds `useTranslator` at its nested node (W14) and builds the label object; the component renders pure data.

## Required pattern

```tsx
// presentational component -- explicit labels, no t
type NotificationRowLabels = {
    titleLabel: string;
    timeLabel: string;
};

export const CustomerNotificationCard: React.FC<{
    labels: NotificationRowLabels;
}> = ({labels}) => (
    <Row>
        <Text>{labels.titleLabel}</Text>
        <Text>{labels.timeLabel}</Text>
    </Row>
);

// screen -- builds labels from its typed translator
const t = useTranslator(tr => tr.ui.pages.customer.notifications);
const labels: NotificationRowLabels = {
    titleLabel: t("titleLabel"),
    timeLabel: t("timeLabel"),
};
<CustomerNotificationCard labels={labels} />
```

## Forbidden

- `t: (key: string) => string` as a prop type on a presentational component.
- Passing a `Translator` instance into a presentational component.
- Calling `t("someKey")` inside a presentational component instead of receiving the resolved string.

